Access Modifiers:
    Access modifiers are keywords in java that help us control the access of instance and static variables they can
    also be used to control the access of methods and classes. There are four access levels and there a three
    keywords in java to apply these access levels.
    Private, protected, default public
Best Practices:
    Instance variables/fields/properties/attributes are private 99% of the time.
    99% of the time constructors are public.
    90% of the time methods are public, 8% private and the rest of the time they're default or protected
